article.headline: IPFW 82, N.J. Tech 65
article.story: FORT WAYNE, Ind. (AP) -- DeWitt Scott came off the bench and scored 17 points to lead IPFW to an 82-65 victory over New Jersey Tech on Saturday. Jaraun Burrows had 15 points on 5-of-10 shooting and Tyler Best added 14 points and five assists for the Mastodons (7-11). Kraig Peters led New Jersey Tech (3-14) with 17 points on 5-of-10 shooting. Nesho Milosevic added 14 points and eight rebounds for the Highlanders. IPFW shot 12-of-27 (44 percent) from the floor in the first half and led 41-36 at halftime. A layup by Burrows with 32 seconds left capped a 13-6 IPFW run and gave the Mastodons their largest lead of 19 points. New Jersey Tech held a 38-23 rebounding edge.
